 The Energy Regulatory Commission has cut the prices of a litre of petrol and diesel by 8 shillings and 80 cents and 7 shillings and 35 cents respectively in Nairobi, following the signing of the finance bill into law by the President which had  revised the vat from 16% to 8%. . Kerosene prices will go up by 10 shillings and 71 cents.  